messages.content: What is ComfyUI Neural network latent upscale custom node?
ComfyUI Neural network latent upscale custom node is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows upscaling the latents quickly using a small neural network without needing to decode and encode with VAE.
Where can the ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale node be found in ComfyUI?
The ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale node can be found in 'Add Node -> latent -> NNLatentUpscale' in ComfyUI.
How is the ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale node meant to be used in a workflow?

The ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale node is meant to be used in a workflow where the initial image is generated in lower resolution, the latent is upscaled and the upscaled latent is fed back into the stable diffusion u-net for low noise diffusion pass (high-res fix).
How much faster is neural net latent upscaling compared to VAE decode -> upscale -> encode?
Compared to VAE decode -> upscale -> encode, the neural net latent upscale is about 20 - 50 times faster depending on the image resolution with minimal quality loss.
What is the difference between neural net upscale and direct linear interpolation of the latent in terms of speed and quality?
Compared to direct linear interpolation of the latent, the neural net upscale is slower but has much better quality. Direct latent interpolation usually has very large artifacts.
How can the ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale repository be installed?
To install the ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale repository, clone it in the ComfyUI 'custom_nodes' directory with the command: 'git clone https://github.com/Ttl/ComfyUi_NNLatentUpscale.git'.
What dataset and resolution were used for evaluating the performance of ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale?
The performance of ComfyUI_NNLatentUpscale was evaluated using the COCO 2017 validation images dataset, center cropped to 256x256 resolution.
